<title type="html"><![CDATA[HTML4 Transitional and HTML5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=93&amp;p=381#p381"><![CDATA[
The object tag could be fixed if all of its attributes were inside quotation marks (&quot; &quot;). The closing &lt;/embed&gt; tag will always show up as invalid in html 3-4 validators. Inside the &lt;embed&gt; tag, the &quot;quality=high&quot; attribute is not part of any html spec and is only used to set up the Flash player.<br /><br />A better tool for custom tags is xml.<br /><br />HTML 5 is expanded from the HTML 4.01/XHTML 1.0 strict spec. It isn't transitional so you can't use some of the HTML 3.2 attributs such as: &lt;p align=&quot;right&quot;&gt;.<br /><br />Don't be so sure that legacy tags are the best way to go. It is only a matter of time before browser support for legacy tags withers. When I upgraded to Opera version 9.21, this HTML 3 embed tag no longer looped a sound clip:<br /><br />&lt;EMBED SRC=&quot;../midimusic/grandfather.mid&quot; width=0 height=5 loop=true autostart=true&gt;<br /><br />(Taken from the <a href="http://www.contemplator.com/folk.html" class="postlink">Contemplator's Folk music site</a>.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">wgabrie</a> — Fri Jul 27, 2007 10:31 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
